{{cpp/ranges/drop_while_view/navbar}}

{{ddcl|since=c++20|
constexpr auto end();
}}

Returns a sentinel or an iterator representing the end of the {{tt|drop_while_view}}.

Effectively returns {{c|ranges::end(base_)}}, where {{rlpi|/#Data members|base_}} is the underlying view.

===Parameters===
(none)

===Return value===
A sentinel or an iterator representing the end of the view.

===Example===
{{example
|code=
#include &lt;cassert&gt;
#include &lt;iostream&gt;
#include &lt;ranges&gt;
 
int main()
{
    static constexpr auto data = {0, -1, -2, 3, 1, 4, 1, 5}; 
    auto view = std::ranges::drop_while_view{data, [](int x) { return x &lt;= 0; }&lt;!----&gt;};
    assert(view.end()[-1] == 5);
}
}}
